2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Croft was born in 1393, in Croft, Herefordshire, England. He had at least 1 son with Mrs William de Croft. He died in 1433, in his hometown, at the age of 40."},"et":{"1393–1433":"1393–1433","1402–Female":"1402–Surnud","1427–1509":"1427–1509","1402":"1402","1433":"1433","1509":"1509","1393":"1393","1427":"1427","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, England","Croft Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1393–1433":"1393–1433","1402–Female":"1402–Kuollut","1427–1509":"1427–1509","1402":"1402","1433":"1433","1509":"1509","1393":"1393","1427":"1427","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, England","Croft Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1393–1433":"1393–1433","1402–Female":"1402–Décédée","1427–1509":"1427–1509","1402":"1402","1433":"1433","1509":"1509","1393":"1393","1427":"1427","Croft, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, Angleterre","Croft Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Croft, Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William de Croft est né en 1393, à Croft, Herefordshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs William de Croft. Il est décédé en 1433, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 40 ans."},"de":{"1393–1433":"1393–1